cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the problem of Named Entity Recognition (NER) using partially annotated training data, which is a common problem in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a constraint-driven iterative algorithm to learn from noisy data, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of distinguishing between true and false negatives, which involves statistical analysis and data processing, making cs.NE (Networks and Communications) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) possible categories as well.
